6. Rights of the data subject
If you are in EU, you have the following rights based General Data Protection Regulation　("GDPR").
(1) Right of accessing personal information(purpose of using, type, destination of sharing, storage term)
(2) Right of request to rectify, delete and/or restrict using personal information
(3) Right of objection to processing of personal information
(4) Right to transfer personal information(right to data portability)
(5) Right to withdrawing your consent
(6) Right to complain to a supervisory authority
7. Personal information security
Ponos will take reasonable and possibility security measures to protect your information from any alteration, loss, misuse or any unauthorized access as far as practically possible. But we do not warrant or represent that your information will be protected absolutely against alteration, loss, or misuse by third parties. And any method of transmission over the Internet is not secure absolutely. Please be careful of your security to use the Internet by yourselves.
8. Data retention period
Ponos retain your information for as long as needed to provide you services, unless we are required by law to delete.
